00:59:27,884 --> 00:59:31,220
<i>Major Powers wants us to die in a loud,
grotesque, military manner.</i>

681
00:59:31,596 --> 00:59:33,598
I don't give a fuck about Major Powers.

682
00:59:33,890 --> 00:59:36,350
My job is to keep you men alive.
Let's move on.

683
00:59:45,651 --> 00:59:48,154
Coming to the ambush site
over the next hill.

684
00:59:48,237 --> 00:59:49,572
Roger that.

685
00:59:49,864 --> 00:59:52,950
<i>It helps, knowing when and where
you're going to be hit, sir.</i>

686
00:59:54,035 --> 00:59:58,706
<i>Easy. Give them a few more yards,
then we'll nail the coffin shut.</i>

687
01:00:02,960 --> 01:00:04,629
Chill out. Here they come.

688
01:00:05,213 --> 01:00:06,881
Hit them now!

689
01:00:07,799 --> 01:00:08,966
Now!

690
01:00:20,019 --> 01:00:21,437
Cease fire!

691
01:00:23,398 --> 01:00:25,817
You're in the wrong ambush site!

692
01:00:27,402 --> 01:00:28,903
Cease fire!

693
01:00:33,324 --> 01:00:35,827
They're in the wrong ambush site!

694
01:00:37,203 --> 01:00:39,789
Recon! Recon!

695
01:00:47,880 --> 01:00:49,716
- Sergeant Major!
- Yes?

696
01:00:50,341 --> 01:00:52,343
Turn this damn thing off.

697
01:00:52,969 --> 01:00:55,638
<i>Makes a hell of a racket, doesn't it, sir?</i>

698
01:00:59,726 --> 01:01:03,104
<i>This man usurped authority,
disregarded procedures...</i>

699
01:01:03,187 --> 01:01:07,608
<i>...and ignored my personal directives
all week. Why, Lieutenant?</i>

700
01:01:07,775 --> 01:01:11,279
<i>- Sir, I thought the training...
- You think too much and act too little.</i>

701
01:01:11,362 --> 01:01:14,907
You're supposed to be an officer.
Look it up in your leader's handbook.

702
01:01:16,951 --> 01:01:20,288
Who gave you permission to deviate
from the training schedule?

703
01:01:20,371 --> 01:01:22,540
<i>I needed to evaluate my men, sir.</i>

704
01:01:22,790 --> 01:01:27,545
<i>They're not your men, you son of a bitch.
They're the U.S. Marine Corps' men.</i>

705
01:01:27,628 --> 01:01:30,882
The 2nd Division's men.
The 8th Marine Regiment's men.

706
01:01:30,965 --> 01:01:33,885
<i>In other words, they're my men.
And so are you. Get it?</i>

707
01:01:34,052 --> 01:01:38,973
I'll get my ass shot off if I'm in a hot
landing zone with an untrained platoon.

708
01:01:39,182 --> 01:01:42,351
You will follow my program to the letter.
No questions asked.

709
01:01:42,435 --> 01:01:45,772
<i>We go into combat tomorrow,
you'll plant half those men.</i>

710
01:01:50,943 --> 01:01:52,737
<i>You did it on your own, didn't you?</i>

711
01:01:52,820 --> 01:01:55,823
I can't fix it if I don't know what's broken.

712
01:01:56,199 --> 01:01:57,992
You make it easy.

713
01:01:58,076 --> 01:01:59,118
Sir...

714
01:01:59,619 --> 01:02:02,580
...I gave Gunney permission
to freelance his...

715
01:02:02,663 --> 01:02:04,999
<i>...I mean, the men, sir.</i>

716
01:02:09,837 --> 01:02:11,255
<i>Wait outside, Ring.</i>

717
01:02:11,589 --> 01:02:12,632
<i>Aye, aye, sir.</i>

718
01:02:16,844 --> 01:02:19,180
<i>I'm going to run you
out of the Corps, Highway.</i>

719
01:02:19,889 --> 01:02:23,226
<i>The funny thing is, you'll do all the work.</i>

720
01:02:24,143 --> 01:02:26,270
<i>Sooner or later, you'll disobey orders...</i>

721
01:02:26,354 --> 01:02:30,274
<i>...circumvent procedures again,
or just get drunk.</i>

722
01:02:30,691 --> 01:02:31,984
You can't help it.

723
01:02:32,360 --> 01:02:36,322
<i>You're too old, too stupid and
too prideful to change.</i>

724
01:02:37,407 --> 01:02:39,409
I'll enjoy watching you fall.

725
01:02:41,369 --> 01:02:43,871
<i>Get out and send in that idiot, Ring.</i>

726
01:02:51,003 --> 01:02:53,089
<i>He wants to see you, Lieutenant.</i>

727
01:02:55,466 --> 01:02:57,802
- I'm sorry.
- No need to be.

728
01:02:58,970 --> 01:03:00,012
Lieutenant?

729
01:03:00,930 --> 01:03:02,181
Recon.

730
01:03:10,898 --> 01:03:12,900
You'll let anybody in here. Won't you?

731
01:03:14,026 --> 01:03:16,362
Have one on the house to ease your pain.

732
01:03:29,042 --> 01:03:32,545
Want to get drunk and howl at the moon...

733
01:03:33,588 --> 01:03:37,091
<i>...get us both busted back to low-ass,
no-rank, mud-rolling PFC?</i>

734
01:03:37,592 --> 01:03:38,926
I'm your man.

735
01:03:39,177 --> 01:03:40,678
<i>What are we, Chooz?</i>

736
01:03:41,888 --> 01:03:46,559
We're short-haired bastards with meat
cleavers for pricks and kerosene for blood.

737
01:03:47,101 --> 01:03:49,437
Yes. We're all of that. That's for sure.

738
01:03:51,064 --> 01:03:52,148
We're 0-1-1.

739
01:03:53,441 --> 01:03:54,609
Say again?

740
01:03:55,735 --> 01:04:00,073
<i>Major Powers, one dark cloudy morning,
said to me, "Sergeant Major...</i>

741
01:04:01,157 --> 01:04:02,825
"...you're 0-1-1.

742
01:04:03,284 --> 01:04:06,829
<i>"No wins. One tie, Korea...</i>

743
01:04:07,455 --> 01:04:09,290
<i>"...and one loss, Vietnam."</i>

744
01:04:12,210 --> 01:04:15,213
<i>Maybe we lost the war,
but we won the battles.</i>

745
01:04:18,049 --> 01:04:21,219
I'm not going to lose the next one
because my men aren't ready.

746
01:04:22,095 --> 01:04:23,554
What are you going to do?

747
01:04:24,305 --> 01:04:25,973
Make them Marines.

748
01:04:27,058 --> 01:04:28,559
Stoney Jackson...

749
01:04:28,935 --> 01:04:33,481
<i>...best goddamned platoon sergeant
two short-pricked, piss-ant...</i>

750
01:04:33,606 --> 01:04:36,317
<i>...baby soldier, little fuckers
ever went to war with.</i>

751
01:04:36,651 --> 01:04:39,153
- Yes. Heartbreak Ridge.
- Heartbreak Ridge.

752
01:04:39,404 --> 01:04:41,072
Your CO called.

753
01:04:41,739 --> 01:04:43,825
Your battalion just went on full alert.

754
01:04:55,670 --> 01:04:57,171
God bless.

755
01:04:59,132 --> 01:05:02,093
- I can't find my tent.
- Where's my poncho liner?

756
01:05:02,176 --> 01:05:04,637
<i>Damn it, who's got my web gear?</i>

757
01:05:04,721 --> 01:05:06,889
<i>Profile, that's my canteen.</i>

758
01:05:07,223 --> 01:05:11,394
Aponte better get back here.
He'll do time for being AWOL.

759
01:05:12,562 --> 01:05:16,733
<i>People, let's have an equipment check.
Weapon?</i>

760
01:05:19,610 --> 01:05:20,903
Let's keep it simple.

761
01:05:20,987 --> 01:05:25,158
<i>You got boots on,
you can walk into combat. Let's go.</i>

762
01:05:29,454 --> 01:05:30,538
Where's Aponte?

763
01:05:30,830 --> 01:05:33,833
He's sick. Must've been the chipped beef.
I'm sick myself.

764
01:05:33,916 --> 01:05:37,253
- You've eaten worse.
- Only when I'm shit-faced.

765
01:05:46,596 --> 01:05:50,266
These DD-13-48 request forms
are not filled out properly.

766
01:05:50,850 --> 01:05:54,729
<i>We're going to approach this in an orderly,
proficient manner, Sergeant Major.</i>

767
01:05:54,812 --> 01:05:55,855
<i>Yes, sir.</i>

768
01:05:57,148 --> 01:05:59,609
I want you to be sure
that each round of ammo...

769
01:05:59,692 --> 01:06:03,529
...is counted and returned
in the same way it was received.

770
01:06:03,821 --> 01:06:08,576
- I'll personally dot the i's and cross the t's.
- Sloppiness breeds inefficiency.

771
01:06:09,577 --> 01:06:12,580
<i>Your outfit could use
some cleaning up, Gunney.</i>

772
01:06:13,331 --> 01:06:16,501
<i>Sir, I want to issue my squad leader
some night vision glasses.</i>

773
01:06:16,876 --> 01:06:20,922
- I should've thought of that.
- That is not part of your TO&E.

774
01:06:21,172 --> 01:06:22,423
I thought it might...

775
01:06:22,507 --> 01:06:26,177
Fill out the proper request forms
and send it through the chain of command.

776
01:06:26,260 --> 01:06:27,512
Request forms?

777
01:06:32,266 --> 01:06:33,309
Attention!

778
01:06:36,229 --> 01:06:38,064
<i>At ease, men.</i>

779
01:06:38,356 --> 01:06:41,984
<i>Major Malcolm Powers, sir.
Annapolis, Class of '71.</i>

780
01:06:43,236 --> 01:06:44,904
<i>How are your men doing, Major?</i>

781
01:06:45,488 --> 01:06:48,908
<i>My men are ready to fight to the death
to protect our country, sir.</i>

782
01:06:50,410 --> 01:06:52,745
Let's hope that won't be necessary.

783
01:06:55,289 --> 01:06:56,958
Have we ever served together?

784
01:06:57,542 --> 01:07:00,294
<i>I don't know, sir.
Sergeant Major Choozoo and I...</i>

785
01:07:00,378 --> 01:07:03,047
<i>...were in the 2nd Battalion
in the 7th in 1968.</i>

786
01:07:03,756 --> 01:07:06,592
<i>I had a rifle company in 1st Battalion, 7th.</i>

787
01:07:07,093 --> 01:07:10,096
<i>We sure as hell chewed
some of the same dirt, sir.</i>

788
01:07:10,638 --> 01:07:14,475
That's for sure.
What's your assessment of this alert?

789
01:07:14,976 --> 01:07:16,561
It's a cluster fuck.

790
01:07:19,981 --> 01:07:21,065
Say again?

791
01:07:21,149 --> 01:07:24,819
<i>Marines are fighting men, sir,
they shouldn't be sitting on their asses...</i>

792
01:07:24,902 --> 01:07:28,656
...filling out forms for equipment
they should already have.

793
01:07:29,574 --> 01:07:31,743
<i>Interesting observation, Gunney.</i>

794
01:07:33,453 --> 01:07:34,579
<i>Carry on, Major.</i>

795
01:07:40,918 --> 01:07:43,254
<i>Now hear this. Now hear this.</i>

796
01:07:43,379 --> 01:07:45,465
This is it. We're going to war.

797
01:07:47,008 --> 01:07:51,262
<i>This has been an emergency deployment
readiness exercise.</i>

798
01:07:51,929 --> 01:07:56,100
<i>We are standing down.
The alert is cancelled.</i>

799
01:07:56,684 --> 01:07:57,935
Damn it.

800
01:07:59,187 --> 01:08:01,189
<i>Maybe next time, sir.</i>

801
01:08:02,231 --> 01:08:04,233
You heard him. Move it out.

802
01:08:13,451 --> 01:08:14,702
Aponte.

803
01:08:15,578 --> 01:08:16,913
<i>Oh, him.</i>

804
01:08:17,246 --> 01:08:18,581
Where is he?

805
01:08:19,165 --> 01:08:20,833
What's wrong with you?

806
01:08:21,250 --> 01:08:23,628
Nobody goes over the hill on me.

807
01:08:24,462 --> 01:08:28,633
<i>If you didn't have those stripes,
I'd kick your ass around the block!</i>

808
01:08:28,841 --> 01:08:30,968
<i>Yes, but since I'm not into violence...</i>

809
01:08:31,052 --> 01:08:34,555
...I'll refrain from kicking your ass
at this particular time.

810
01:08:34,680 --> 01:08:36,682
I'll give you a rebate on your life.

811
01:08:37,350 --> 01:08:39,685
<i>Besides, who the hell is Aponte?</i>

812
01:08:39,811 --> 01:08:42,814
He ain't heavy
and he sure the hell ain't my brother.

813
01:08:44,232 --> 01:08:45,274
Gunney Highway.

814
01:08:45,691 --> 01:08:47,693
That's right. Gunney Highway.

815
01:08:48,111 --> 01:08:49,362
Come in.

816
01:08:49,821 --> 01:08:52,281
<i>I'm sorry, but I had to tell him.</i>

817
01:08:52,365 --> 01:08:55,493
<i>This is my wife, Sara.
Clean that up a little, honey.</i>

818
01:08:55,743 --> 01:08:58,413
<i>Gunney, I filled out all the forms there are.</i>

819
01:08:58,830 --> 01:09:01,791
What the Corps could give
just isn't enough for the family.

820
01:09:02,166 --> 01:09:03,292
So I took a job.

821
01:09:03,376 --> 01:09:05,420
- You got a job?
- Yes.

822
01:09:05,795 --> 01:09:08,881
- You want out of the Marines?
- No! No way.

823
01:09:09,382 --> 01:09:12,969
<i>Then we're going to have to cut through
all the red tape B.S., aren't we?</i>

824
01:09:13,052 --> 01:09:14,637
<i>- Yes, we are.
- Knock it off.</i>

825
01:09:16,931 --> 01:09:19,767
Here. Here's a special fund.
Gunnery sergeants only.

826
01:09:23,187 --> 01:09:25,189
<i>Don't worry, you can pay it back.</i>

827
01:09:25,898 --> 01:09:29,110
- Here. You better take him. Jesus Christ.
- Thank you.

828
01:09:37,660 --> 01:09:41,080
- What are you smiling at?
- I always knew you were Santa Claus.

829
01:09:41,164 --> 01:09:44,083
You pull another suckhead play like that...

830
01:09:44,167 --> 01:09:47,420
...the only thing that will beat you
to the brig is an ambulance.

831
01:09:47,503 --> 01:09:49,756
<i>Yes, sir, Gunnery Sergeant Highway, sir.</i>

832
01:09:54,427 --> 01:09:56,763
You can't leave the Duke of Cool!

833
01:09:57,055 --> 01:09:58,890
This man has no social graces.

834
01:10:03,978 --> 01:10:05,146
So?

835
01:10:06,189 --> 01:10:08,858
Lureen down at the Palace
said you had the night off.

836
01:10:09,567 --> 01:10:11,235
Lureen talks too much.

837
01:10:11,736 --> 01:10:13,404
Can I buy you a beer?

838
01:10:16,949 --> 01:10:18,284
Jesus.

839
01:10:20,620 --> 01:10:24,957
<i>You can't come back after all this time,
with no warning whatsoever.</i>

840
01:10:25,291 --> 01:10:28,628
<i>Interfere at my place of work,
almost started a brawl...</i>

841
01:10:28,961 --> 01:10:31,798
...almost lost me the only crummy job
I could find.

842
01:10:32,131 --> 01:10:35,385
<i>Then you show up here,
expecting me to just smooth as silk...</i>

843
01:10:35,468 --> 01:10:37,804
...invite you in for a sit-down and a smile.

844
01:10:38,137 --> 01:10:40,973
<i>It's always the same, Highway.
All balls, no brains.</i>

845
01:10:42,642 --> 01:10:44,477
Is there something you're afraid of?

846
01:10:44,811 --> 01:10:48,940
Yes. I'm afraid I'll dent that
thick skull of yours with this frying pan.

847
01:10:51,651 --> 01:10:56,030
<i>- It wouldn't be the first time, would it?
- No.</i>

848
01:10:59,659 --> 01:11:01,327
Nice place you have here.

849
01:11:03,204 --> 01:11:05,748
Thanks. You want a glass?

850
01:11:17,343 --> 01:11:21,764
- Feet still bothersome?
- I hawk booze five nights a week.

851
01:11:23,099 --> 01:11:26,102
There's no senior prom
looming on my horizon.

852
01:11:27,353 --> 01:11:29,021
To the old times.

853
01:11:29,522 --> 01:11:31,858
Just as long as you don't say good times.

854
01:11:32,191 --> 01:11:34,360
<i>We had our share of those, too, didn't we?</i>

855
01:11:35,111 --> 01:11:37,363
I don't know. I can't think that far back.

856
01:11:38,448 --> 01:11:40,032
How are you feeling?

857
01:11:40,450 --> 01:11:41,784
Terrific.

858
01:11:42,034 --> 01:11:44,036
Absolutely couldn't feel better.

859
01:11:48,541 --> 01:11:50,209
What brings you here?

860
01:11:51,377 --> 01:11:54,213
<i>I'm back with Recon, back where I belong.</i>

861
01:11:57,050 --> 01:11:58,259
So?

862
01:11:58,551 --> 01:12:00,553
It's different this time.

863
01:12:02,722 --> 01:12:03,806
How?

864
01:12:05,058 --> 01:12:09,228
I'm coming to the end of it.
I don't know where I go from here.

865
01:12:09,479 --> 01:12:13,149
I just want it to end
as right as it was when I started.

866
01:12:16,736 --> 01:12:20,239
Do you want some chips? There's pretzels.

867
01:12:21,908 --> 01:12:22,950
<i>Yes, thanks.</i>

868
01:12:23,910 --> 01:12:25,912
Fringe benefits of work.

869
01:12:26,746 --> 01:12:28,247
Tell me something.

870
01:12:29,248 --> 01:12:32,251
Did we mutually nurture each other?

871
01:12:33,753 --> 01:12:35,171
I beg your pardon?

872
01:12:35,588 --> 01:12:38,800
Did we communicate in a meaningful way
in our relationship?

873
01:12:39,759 --> 01:12:41,594
Relationship?

874
01:12:45,431 --> 01:12:47,600
<i>Hell, I thought we were married.</i>

875
01:12:49,268 --> 01:12:51,938
I've been thinking about the past lately.

876
01:12:54,107 --> 01:12:56,275
I was just wondering what went wrong.

877
01:12:57,276 --> 01:12:58,611
With what?

878
01:13:00,113 --> 01:13:01,447
With me.

879
01:13:02,281 --> 01:13:04,117
The Corps. With us.

880
01:13:08,955 --> 01:13:11,124
That is so damn much like you.

881
01:13:11,332 --> 01:13:16,170
You never could see that things just don't
fit neatly into right and wrong.

882
01:13:16,963 --> 01:13:18,381
What else is there?

883
01:13:20,466 --> 01:13:22,135
It isn't that simple.

884
01:13:25,805 --> 01:13:28,975
I went by those rooms that we rented
when we got married.

885
01:13:29,308 --> 01:13:30,977
<i>Damn, they're small.</i>

886
01:13:33,479 --> 01:13:36,315
They say everything shrinks with age.

887
01:13:40,319 --> 01:13:41,821
Tell me something.

888
01:13:43,489 --> 01:13:45,825
What did you want out of our marriage?

889
01:13:49,162 --> 01:13:52,331
We talked once about an avocado ranch...

890
01:13:52,582 --> 01:13:55,251
...about buying a house
with a barbecue in the back.

891
01:13:55,668 --> 01:14:00,173
But then you'd volunteer for every damn
war that came down the pike.

892
01:14:04,677 --> 01:14:06,345
- Goddamn it!
- What's the matter?

893
01:14:06,846 --> 01:14:08,848
How could I be so stupid?

894
01:14:09,265 --> 01:14:10,767
What do you mean?

895
01:14:11,017 --> 01:14:15,396
- You changed tactics on me!
- What are you talking about?

896
01:14:15,480 --> 01:14:18,149
<i>Gave up the old frontal assault,
tried to outflank me.</i>

897
01:14:18,232 --> 01:14:21,402
<i>I am onto you, Highway,
and I want you out of here, right now!</i>

898
01:14:21,694 --> 01:14:25,615
You're not acting very dignified
for a mature woman.

899
01:14:27,366 --> 01:14:32,205
<i>You old fucking Marine warhorse,
I'll show you dignified!</i>

900
01:14:32,622 --> 01:14:36,793
You get out of here! Go on!
Get the fuck out of here!

901
01:14:38,044 --> 01:14:40,922
You better get your tail out of here
or I'll get mad!

902
01:14:41,005 --> 01:14:43,049
<i>Take that, you old fuck!</i>

903
01:14:43,383 --> 01:14:47,553
<i>I never want to see your craggy,
old face again, you hear?</i>

904
01:14:47,887 --> 01:14:51,057
Don't ever come back. Ever!

905
01:14:52,725 --> 01:14:55,728
<i>She's as crazy as she's always been,
for Christ's sake.</i>

906
01:14:57,397 --> 01:14:59,065
You asshole!

907
01:15:04,404 --> 01:15:06,572
<i>I hate you, Highway!</i>

908
01:15:08,825 --> 01:15:10,034
Fuck you!

909
01:15:23,339 --> 01:15:24,590
<i>Tonight's winner...</i>

910
01:15:25,758 --> 01:15:28,010
<i>... is Miss Sarita Dwayne!</i>

