You hear me?

1301
01:56:22,590 --> 01:56:26,010
- I thought you were dead.
- Wishful thinking.

1302
01:56:31,099 --> 01:56:33,393
<i>Lieutenant, what are we waiting for?</i>

1303
01:56:34,602 --> 01:56:38,731
<i>All right, you devil dogs,
let's take that fucking hill!</i>

1304
01:58:58,121 --> 01:58:59,122
Go!

1305
01:59:10,133 --> 01:59:11,676
Get them out of there.

1306
01:59:13,219 --> 01:59:15,263
Move it! Get your hands up!

1307
01:59:36,868 --> 01:59:38,161
<i>All secure, sir!</i>

1308
01:59:38,995 --> 01:59:41,039
<i>- Corporal Jones!
- Yes, sir!</i>

1309
01:59:43,166 --> 01:59:44,417
Move them out.

1310
01:59:44,500 --> 01:59:46,294
<i>You heard him, men! Move them out!</i>

1311
02:00:27,794 --> 02:00:30,797
Just what the hell do you think
you were doing?

1312
02:00:35,051 --> 02:00:37,261
<i>Just enjoying the view, sir.</i>

1313
02:00:38,763 --> 02:00:40,390
You disobeyed a direct order.

1314
02:00:42,058 --> 02:00:45,728
I told you to stay in contact
and not take this hill without me.

1315
02:00:48,064 --> 02:00:50,024
<i>Get on your feet, Highway!</i>

1316
02:00:52,276 --> 02:00:56,489
<i>With all due respect, sir,
you're beginning to bore the hell out of me.</i>

1317
02:01:33,276 --> 02:01:36,112
<i>- Who's in charge here?
- I am, sir. Major Malcolm Powers.</i>

1318
02:01:36,696 --> 02:01:38,239
Did you lead this assault?

1319
02:01:39,365 --> 02:01:43,036
<i>Lieutenant Ring and Gunnery Sergeant
Highway disobeyed a direct order, sir.</i>

1320
02:01:43,953 --> 02:01:47,290
<i>I told them to wait for support,
but they still charged this hill.</i>

1321
02:01:47,540 --> 02:01:48,624
Why?

1322
02:01:48,833 --> 02:01:51,753
<i>Because we're paid to improvise, sir.
To overcome, to adapt.</i>

1323
02:01:51,836 --> 02:01:53,963
<i>I gave the order to take this hill, sir.</i>

1324
02:01:54,255 --> 02:01:56,549
<i>Ring, this is going to ruin your career.</i>

1325
02:01:58,509 --> 02:02:02,013
<i>- Are you new to the infantry, Major?
- Yes, sir. I came over from Supply.</i>

1326
02:02:02,138 --> 02:02:03,931
<i>- Were you good at that?
- Yes, sir!</i>

1327
02:02:04,390 --> 02:02:08,436
<i>Then stick to it, because you're
a cluster fuck as an infantry officer.</i>

1328
02:02:08,603 --> 02:02:10,730
<i>This is a Marine Amphibious Unit, Major.</i>

1329
02:02:10,855 --> 02:02:12,482
My men are hard chargers.

1330
02:02:12,565 --> 02:02:15,318
Ring and Highway
took a handful of young fire-pissers...

1331
02:02:15,443 --> 02:02:18,154
<i>...exercised some personal initiative,
and kicked ass!</i>

1332
02:02:20,490 --> 02:02:22,533
<i>- Good work, Lieutenant.
- Thank you, sir!</i>

1333
02:02:23,076 --> 02:02:26,579
<i>Lieutenant, see that those students
are escorted back to Cherry Point.</i>

1334
02:02:29,082 --> 02:02:30,541
You're dismissed!

1335
02:02:51,354 --> 02:02:54,524
What are you two sorry-assed individuals
looking at?

1336
02:02:54,649 --> 02:02:56,275
Get out of my LZ.

1337
02:02:57,860 --> 02:02:59,404
<i>Semper Fi.</i>

1338
02:03:04,283 --> 02:03:07,537
<i>Chooz, I guess we're not 0-1-1 now.</i>

1339
02:03:47,410 --> 02:03:49,287
- There's my family.
- All right.

1340
02:03:49,912 --> 02:03:51,706
- Got anybody here?
- No.

1341
02:03:51,789 --> 02:03:55,543
But it's a beautiful day
and I'm ready to play.

1342
02:03:55,668 --> 02:03:58,671
<i>- Give them hell, man.
- Definitely.</i>

1343
02:04:11,309 --> 02:04:15,772
<i>Like I said, I'm ready to play.
You know what I mean?</i>

1344
02:04:16,314 --> 02:04:18,274
<i>Anytime, man.</i>

1345
02:04:18,775 --> 02:04:20,318
You'll be a civilian soon.

1346
02:04:20,401 --> 02:04:24,781
<i>Grow your hair long, sleep late,
become an asshole rock and roll star.</i>

1347
02:04:25,615 --> 02:04:28,618
Sergeant Major Choozoo
gave me re-up papers.

1348
02:04:28,868 --> 02:04:30,328
And you signed them?

1349
02:04:30,453 --> 02:04:33,456
<i>Yes, Gunney,
I'm a better Marine than I was a singer.</i>

1350
02:04:33,873 --> 02:04:36,626
<i>You're also a lot dumber
than I thought you were, too.</i>

1351
02:04:36,709 --> 02:04:37,960
What about you?

1352
02:04:38,920 --> 02:04:43,049
<i>No, I've had it.
No room in this man's Corps for me now.</i>

1353
02:04:43,633 --> 02:04:45,593
<i>Besides, they've got you.</i>

1354
02:05:07,156 --> 02:05:11,160
I guess all of these marching bands
and parades are old stuff to you.

1355
02:05:12,286 --> 02:05:14,664
<i>To tell you the truth, this is the first time.</i>

1356
02:05:15,498 --> 02:05:18,000
There are my ladies.

1357
02:05:18,126 --> 02:05:20,253
<i>Gunney, duty calls.</i>
